# Bar data utilities in Python

This package includes utilities and a plugin model to fetch and manipulate bar data
for stocks and financials markets from various providers. This is work in progress.

Bar data is represented as a datafrane with a `date` or `datetime` index
and `open`, `high`, `low`, `close`, `volume` columns all in lower case.
Data for stocks prices is assumed adjusted by default.

The main conventions are:
- data sources are referenced by a single `source` parameter
- all sources accept similar frequencies with the `freq` parameter
- maximum number of bars is indicated with the `max_bars` parameter
- both `start_date` and `end_date` parameters are optional

## Typical Usage

```python
from bardata import get_prices

TICKER = "AAPL" 
SOURCE = 'sample'
FREQ = 'daily'

prices = get_prices(ticker, freq=FREQ, source=SOURCE)
```

## Related Projects & Resources

- [findatapy](https://github.com/cuemacro/findatapy) Python library to download
market data via Bloomberg, Eikon, Quandl, Yahoo etc.
